issue.title: fileOrDefault method
issue.body:
### Consul Template version

Run `consul-template -v` to show the version. If you are not
running the latest version, please upgrade before submitting an
issue.

`consul-template v0.32.0 (a926131)`

### Expected behavior

The fact that the `file` function always returns an error if the file doesn't exist is a problem for me.  I'd really like to have a `fileOrDefault` version as an analog of the [`keyOrDefault`](https://github.com/hashicorp/consul-template/blob/main/docs/templating-language.md#keyordefault) function.

### Actual behavior
`consul-template` crashes if the file doesn't exist.

issue.title: `make build` not working, returns "No rule to make target `build'"
issue.body:
Quick question.
After downloading the source code, I run `make build` as instructed in readme, but got this error.

```
➜  consul-template git:(main) make build
make: *** No rule to make target `build'.  Stop.
```

I am in the correct directory, same directory as Makefile.

Am I missing something.

issue.title: Skip rendering template block
issue.body:
Is it possible to have a block that will not be rendered by consul-template? I couldn't find anything in the docs.

```
{{ key "service/redis/maxconns" }}   - this gets read from consul

{% raw % }
{{ key "service/redis/maxconns" }} - this is left as is
{% endraw % } 
```

The use for this would be when rendering template in two steps, for example your CI generates nomad job file that contains consul-template syntax for consul to render on runtime.

comment.body:
For others who have this problem, I found that the solution for me was to use a combination of both since I needed to survive two rounds of `consul-template`.

So a

```
{{ file "test" }}
```

where the `test` file contained:

```
{{ `{{ env "NOMAD_PORT_tcp" }}` }}
```
